lign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=oskher@lighttanksofdaoc>Oskher</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Initiate</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#000000>(12/12/02 2:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=16.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Savagery Buffs</span><hr size=1> I currently have a level 7 Valkyn Savage, stats are Str 69 with items, Dex 78, and Qui 77.  I'm spec'ing H2H and Savagery.  I found out early that the Dps buff is so negligable at this level that it does not even register.  In other words when I attack and hit I do not get, &quot;You have hit so-and-so for X additional points od damage&quot;, so I no longer use the Dps buff.  I do use the parry and haste buffs and on occasion the evade buff.  I definately see a difference with all three.  I can usually end up parrying anywhere from 2 to 4 blows from blue and yellow con mobs which is plenty with haste buff rolling.  As far as evade goes, I usually only use it when fighting yellow mobs and I do evade 1 or 2 times during a fight.  I will probably use it more often once I get Totemic Fear at level 21, since it's triggered off of evade.  So to sum it up, IMHO the Savage's parry, evade, and haste buffs are definately worth using.<br>
<br>
One thing to note, I was out solo'ing the other day when a Shaman was nice enough to give me a damage add buff and a End regen buff.  With these two buffs I was able to solo orange mygga's with no difficulty at level 6.<br>
